{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Thank you so much. It's really scary to be here"},{"time":4000,"text":"among the smartest of the smart."},{"time":7000,"text":"I'm here to tell you a few tales of passion."},{"time":11000,"text":"There's a Jewish saying that I love."},{"time":14000,"text":"What is truer than truth? Answer: The story."},{"time":21000,"text":"I'm a storyteller. I want to convey something that is truer than truth"},{"time":26000,"text":"about our common humanity."},{"time":28000,"text":"All stories interest me, and some haunt me"},{"time":31000,"text":"until I end up writing them."},{"time":34000,"text":"Certain themes keep coming up:"},{"time":36000,"text":"justice, loyalty, violence, death, political and social issues,"},{"time":42000,"text":"freedom."},{"time":44000,"text":"I'm aware of the mystery around us,"},{"time":47000,"text":"so I write about coincidences, premonitions,"},{"time":50000,"text":"emotions, dreams, the power of nature, magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"In the last 20 years I have published a few books,"},{"time":59000,"text":"but I have lived in anonymity until February of 2006,"},{"time":64000,"text":"when I carried the Olympic flag in the Winter Olympics in Italy."},{"time":68000,"text":"That made me a celebrity. Now people recognize me in Macy's,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and my grandchildren think that I'm cool."},{"time":76000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":77000,"text":"Allow me to tell you about my four minutes of fame."},{"time":80000,"text":"One of the organizers of the Olympic ceremony,"},{"time":83000,"text":"of the opening ceremony,"},{"time":85000,"text":"called me and said that I had been selected"},{"time":87000,"text":"to be one of the flag-bearers."},{"time":90000,"text":"I replied that surely this was a case of mistaken identity"},{"time":93000,"text":"because I'm as far as you can get from being an athlete."},{"time":96000,"text":"Actually, I wasn't even sure that I could go around the stadium"},{"time":99000,"text":"without a walker."},{"time":100000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":102000,"text":"I was told that this was no laughing matter."},{"time":105000,"text":"This would be the first time"},{"time":106000,"text":"that only women would carry the Olympic flag."},{"time":109000,"text":"Five women, representing five continents,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and three Olympic gold medal winners."},{"time":116000,"text":"My first question was, naturally,"},{"time":118000,"text":"what was I going to wear?"},{"time":120000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":121000,"text":"A uniform, she said,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and asked for my measurements."},{"time":125000,"text":"My measurements."},{"time":126000,"text":"I had a vision of myself in a fluffy anorak,"},{"time":129000,"text":"looking like the Michelin Man."},{"time":131000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"By the middle of February,"},{"time":134000,"text":"I found myself in Turin, where enthusiastic crowds"},{"time":137000,"text":"cheered when any of the 80 Olympic teams was in the street."},{"time":142000,"text":"Those athletes had sacrificed everything to compete in the games."},{"time":147000,"text":"They all deserved to win, but there's the element of luck."},{"time":151000,"text":"A speck of snow, an inch of ice, the force of the wind,"},{"time":155000,"text":"can determine the result of a race or a game."},{"time":159000,"text":"However, what matters most -- more than training or luck -- is the heart."},{"time":165000,"text":"Only a fearless and determined heart will get the gold medal."},{"time":170000,"text":"It is all about passion."},{"time":172000,"text":"The streets of Turin were covered with red posters"},{"time":176000,"text":"announcing the slogan of the Olympics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Passion lives here. Isn't it always true?"},{"time":184000,"text":"Heart is what drives us and determines our fate."},{"time":188000,"text":"That is what I need for my characters in my books:"},{"time":192000,"text":"a passionate heart."},{"time":194000,"text":"I need mavericks, dissidents, adventurers, outsiders and rebels,"},{"time":199000,"text":"who ask questions, bend the rules and take risks."},{"time":203000,"text":"People like all of you in this room."},{"time":206000,"text":"Nice people with common sense do not make interesting characters."},{"time":211000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":212000,"text":"They only make good former spouses."},{"time":214000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":216000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"In the green room of the stadium, I met the other flag bearers:"},{"time":222000,"text":"three athletes, and the actresses Susan Sarandon and Sophia Loren."},{"time":228000,"text":"Also, two women with passionate hearts:"},{"time":230000,"text":"Wangari Maathai, the Nobel prizewinner from Kenya"},{"time":234000,"text":"who has planted 30 million trees. And by doing so,"},{"time":237000,"text":"she has changed the soil, the weather,"},{"time":240000,"text":"in some places in Africa, and of course"},{"time":243000,"text":"the economic conditions in many villages."},{"time":246000,"text":"And Somaly Mam, a Cambodian activist who fights passionately"},{"time":251000,"text":"against child prostitution."},{"time":253000,"text":"When she was 14 years old, her grandfather sold her to a brothel."},{"time":258000,"text":"She told us of little girls raped by men who believe that"},{"time":262000,"text":"having sex with a very young virgin will cure them from AIDS."},{"time":266000,"text":"And of brothels where children are forced to receive five,"},{"time":270000,"text":"15 clients per day,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and if they rebel, they are tortured with electricity."},{"time":277000,"text":"In the green room I received my uniform."},{"time":280000,"text":"It was not the kind of outfit that I normally wear,"},{"time":283000,"text":"but it was far from the Michelin Man suit"},{"time":285000,"text":"that I had anticipated. Not bad, really."},{"time":288000,"text":"I looked like a refrigerator."},{"time":290000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":291000,"text":"But so did most of the flag-bearers, except Sophia Loren,"},{"time":295000,"text":"the universal symbol of beauty and passion."},{"time":298000,"text":"Sophia is over 70 and she looks great."},{"time":302000,"text":"She's sexy, slim and tall, with a deep tan."},{"time":306000,"text":"Now, how can you have a deep tan and have no wrinkles?"},{"time":310000,"text":"I don't know."},{"time":311000,"text":"When asked in a TV interview, \"How could she look so good?\""},{"time":316000,"text":"She replied, \"Posture. My back is always straight,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and I don't make old people's noises.\""},{"time":323000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":325000,"text":"So, there you have some free advice"},{"time":327000,"text":"from one of the most beautiful women on earth."},{"time":330000,"text":"No grunting, no coughing, no wheezing,"},{"time":333000,"text":"no talking to yourselves, no farting."},{"time":335000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":336000,"text":"Well, she didn't say that exactly."},{"time":338000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"At some point around midnight,"},{"time":342000,"text":"we were summoned to the wings of the stadium,"},{"time":344000,"text":"and the loudspeakers announced the Olympic flag, and the music started --"},{"time":348000,"text":"by the way, the same music that starts here,"},{"time":350000,"text":"the Aida March."},{"time":352000,"text":"Sophia Loren was right in front of me -- she's a foot taller than I am,"},{"time":357000,"text":"not counting the poofy hair."},{"time":359000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":360000,"text":"She walked elegantly, like a giraffe on the African savannah,"},{"time":365000,"text":"holding the flag on her shoulder. I jogged behind"},{"time":369000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":370000,"text":"-- on my tiptoes -- holding the flag on my extended arm,"},{"time":375000,"text":"so that my head was actually under the damn flag."},{"time":378000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":380000,"text":"All the cameras were, of course, on Sophia."},{"time":383000,"text":"That was fortunate for me, because in most press photos"},{"time":386000,"text":"I appear too, although often between Sophia's legs."},{"time":390000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":392000,"text":"A place where most men would love to be."},{"time":395000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":396000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"The best four minutes of my entire life"},{"time":402000,"text":"were those in the Olympic stadium."},{"time":404000,"text":"My husband is offended when I say this --"},{"time":407000,"text":"although I have explained to him that what we do in private"},{"time":410000,"text":"usually takes less than four minutes --"},{"time":412000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":413000,"text":"-- so he shouldn't take it personally."},{"time":416000,"text":"I have all the press clippings of those four magnificent minutes,"},{"time":420000,"text":"because I don't want to forget them"},{"time":422000,"text":"when old age destroys my brain cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"I want to carry in my heart forever the key word of the Olympics --"},{"time":429000,"text":"passion."},{"time":431000,"text":"So here's a tale of passion."},{"time":434000,"text":"The year is 1998, the place is a prison camp"},{"time":438000,"text":"for Tutsi refugees in Congo."},{"time":440000,"text":"By the way, 80 percent of all refugees and displaced people in the world"},{"time":446000,"text":"are women and girls."},{"time":448000,"text":"We can call this place in Congo a death camp,"},{"time":451000,"text":"because those who are not killed will die of disease or starvation."},{"time":456000,"text":"The protagonists of this story"},{"time":459000,"text":"are a young woman, Rose Mapendo, and her children."},{"time":463000,"text":"She's pregnant and a widow."},{"time":465000,"text":"Soldiers have forced her to watch"},{"time":467000,"text":"as her husband was tortured and killed."},{"time":470000,"text":"Somehow she manages to keep her seven children alive,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and a few months later, she gives birth to premature twins."},{"time":478000,"text":"Two tiny little boys."},{"time":480000,"text":"She cuts the umbilical cord with a stick,"},{"time":483000,"text":"and ties it with her own hair."},{"time":486000,"text":"She names the twins after the camp's commanders"},{"time":489000,"text":"to gain their favor, and feeds them with black tea"},{"time":493000,"text":"because her milk cannot sustain them."},{"time":496000,"text":"When the soldiers burst in her cell to rape her oldest daughter,"},{"time":499000,"text":"she grabs hold of her and refuses to let go,"},{"time":502000,"text":"even when they hold a gun to her head."},{"time":506000,"text":"Somehow, the family survives for 16 months,"},{"time":510000,"text":"and then, by extraordinary luck, and the passionate heart"},{"time":514000,"text":"of a young American man, Sasha Chanoff,"},{"time":519000,"text":"who manages to put her in a U.S. rescue plane,"},{"time":523000,"text":"Rose Mapendo and her nine children end up in Phoenix, Arizona,"},{"time":528000,"text":"where they're now living and thriving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"Mapendo, in Swahili, means great love."},{"time":539000,"text":"The protagonists of my books are strong and passionate women"},{"time":542000,"text":"like Rose Mapendo."},{"time":543000,"text":"I don't make them up. There's no need for that."},{"time":546000,"text":"I look around and I see them everywhere."},{"time":549000,"text":"I have worked with women and for women all my life."},{"time":552000,"text":"I know them well."},{"time":554000,"text":"I was born in ancient times, at the end of the world,"},{"time":558000,"text":"in a patriarchal Catholic and conservative family."},{"time":562000,"text":"No wonder that by age five I was a raging feminist --"},{"time":566000,"text":"although the term had not reached Chile yet,"},{"time":569000,"text":"so nobody knew what the heck was wrong with me."},{"time":571000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":573000,"text":"I would soon find out that there was a high price to pay"},{"time":576000,"text":"for my freedom, and for questioning the patriarchy."},{"time":579000,"text":"But I was happy to pay it, because for every blow that I received,"},{"time":583000,"text":"I was able to deliver two."},{"time":585000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":587000,"text":"Once, when my daughter Paula was in her twenties,"},{"time":589000,"text":"she said to me that feminism was dated, that I should move on."},{"time":594000,"text":"We had a memorable fight. Feminism is dated?"},{"time":598000,"text":"Yes, for privileged women like my daughter and all of us here today,"},{"time":603000,"text":"but not for most of our sisters in the rest of the world"},{"time":606000,"text":"who are still forced into premature marriage,"},{"time":609000,"text":"prostitution, forced labor --"},{"time":612000,"text":"they have children that they don't want or they cannot feed."},{"time":616000,"text":"They have no control over their bodies or their lives."},{"time":619000,"text":"They have no education and no freedom."},{"time":622000,"text":"They are raped, beaten up and sometimes killed with impunity."},{"time":627000,"text":"For most Western young women of today,"},{"time":629000,"text":"being called a feminist is an insult."},{"time":632000,"text":"Feminism has never been sexy, but let me assure you"},{"time":635000,"text":"that it never stopped me from flirting,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and I have seldom suffered from lack of men."},{"time":640000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":642000,"text":"Feminism is not dead, by no means."},{"time":644000,"text":"It has evolved. If you don't like the term,"},{"time":648000,"text":"change it, for Goddess' sake."},{"time":649000,"text":"Call it Aphrodite, or Venus, or bimbo, or whatever you want;"},{"time":654000,"text":"the name doesn't matter,"},{"time":655000,"text":"as long as we understand what it is about, and we support it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"So here's another tale of passion, and this is a sad one."},{"time":664000,"text":"The place is a small women's clinic in a village in Bangladesh."},{"time":668000,"text":"The year is 2005."},{"time":671000,"text":"Jenny is a young American dental hygienist"},{"time":674000,"text":"who has gone to the clinic as a volunteer"},{"time":676000,"text":"during her three-week vacation."},{"time":679000,"text":"She's prepared to clean teeth,"},{"time":681000,"text":"but when she gets there, she finds out that there are no doctors,"},{"time":684000,"text":"no dentists, and the clinic is just a hut full of flies."},{"time":689000,"text":"Outside, there is a line of women"},{"time":691000,"text":"who have waited several hours to be treated."},{"time":694000,"text":"The first patient is in excruciating pain"},{"time":697000,"text":"because she has several rotten molars."},{"time":700000,"text":"Jenny realizes that the only solution is to pull out the bad teeth."},{"time":704000,"text":"She's not licensed for that; she has never done it."},{"time":708000,"text":"She risks a lot and she's terrified."},{"time":710000,"text":"She doesn't even have the proper instruments,"},{"time":713000,"text":"but fortunately she has brought some Novocaine."},{"time":717000,"text":"Jenny has a brave and passionate heart."},{"time":721000,"text":"She murmurs a prayer and she goes ahead with the operation."},{"time":725000,"text":"At the end, the relieved patient kisses her hands."},{"time":729000,"text":"That day the hygienist pulls out many more teeth."},{"time":733000,"text":"The next morning, when she comes again to the so-called clinic,"},{"time":737000,"text":"her first patient is waiting for her with her husband."},{"time":741000,"text":"The woman's face looks like a watermelon."},{"time":744000,"text":"It is so swollen that you can't even see the eyes."},{"time":748000,"text":"The husband, furious, threatens to kill the American."},{"time":751000,"text":"Jenny is horrified at what she has done,"},{"time":755000,"text":"but then the translator explains"},{"time":758000,"text":"that the patient's condition has nothing to do with the operation."},{"time":762000,"text":"The day before, her husband beat her up because she was not home"},{"time":766000,"text":"in time to prepare dinner for him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"Millions of women live like this today."},{"time":773000,"text":"They are the poorest of the poor."},{"time":776000,"text":"Although women do two-thirds of the world's labor,"},{"time":779000,"text":"they own less than one percent of the world's assets."},{"time":783000,"text":"They are paid less than men for the same work"},{"time":786000,"text":"if they're paid at all, and they remain vulnerable"},{"time":790000,"text":"because they have no economic independence,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and they are constantly threatened by exploitation,"},{"time":795000,"text":"violence and abuse."},{"time":797000,"text":"It is a fact that giving women education, work,"},{"time":800000,"text":"the ability to control their own income,"},{"time":802000,"text":"inherit and own property, benefits the society."},{"time":806000,"text":"If a woman is empowered,"},{"time":808000,"text":"her children and her family will be better off."},{"time":811000,"text":"If families prosper, the village prospers,"},{"time":814000,"text":"and eventually so does the whole country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"Wangari Maathai goes to a village in Kenya."},{"time":819000,"text":"She talks with the women and explains that the land is barren"},{"time":823000,"text":"because they have cut and sold the trees."},{"time":825000,"text":"She gets the women to plant new trees and water them,"},{"time":829000,"text":"drop by drop."},{"time":830000,"text":"In a matter of five or six years, they have a forest,"},{"time":834000,"text":"the soil is enriched, and the village is saved."},{"time":838000,"text":"The poorest and most backward societies"},{"time":840000,"text":"are always those that put women down."},{"time":844000,"text":"Yet this obvious truth is ignored by governments"},{"time":847000,"text":"and also by philanthropy."},{"time":849000,"text":"For every dollar given to a women's program,"},{"time":852000,"text":"20 dollars are given to men's programs."},{"time":856000,"text":"Women are 51 percent of humankind."},{"time":859000,"text":"Empowering them will change everything --"},{"time":861000,"text":"more than technology and design and entertainment."},{"time":865000,"text":"I can promise you that women working together --"},{"time":869000,"text":"linked, informed and educated --"},{"time":871000,"text":"can bring peace and prosperity to this forsaken planet."},{"time":876000,"text":"In any war today, most of the casualties are civilians,"},{"time":880000,"text":"mainly women and children. They are collateral damage."},{"time":884000,"text":"Men run the world, and look at the mess we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"What kind of world do we want?"},{"time":890000,"text":"This is a fundamental question that most of us are asking."},{"time":894000,"text":"Does it make sense to participate in the existing world order?"},{"time":899000,"text":"We want a world where life is preserved"},{"time":902000,"text":"and the quality of life is enriched for everybody,"},{"time":905000,"text":"not only for the privileged."},{"time":908000,"text":"In January I saw an exhibit of Fernando Botero's paintings"},{"time":912000,"text":"at the UC Berkeley library."},{"time":915000,"text":"No museum or gallery in the United States,"},{"time":918000,"text":"except for the New York gallery that carries Botero's work,"},{"time":922000,"text":"has dared to show the paintings because the theme"},{"time":925000,"text":"is the Abu Ghraib prison."},{"time":927000,"text":"They are huge paintings of torture and abuse of power,"},{"time":931000,"text":"in the voluminous Botero style."},{"time":934000,"text":"I have not been able to get those images out of my mind"},{"time":938000,"text":"or my heart."},{"time":940000,"text":"What I fear most is power with impunity."},{"time":944000,"text":"I fear abuse of power, and the power to abuse."},{"time":947000,"text":"In our species, the alpha males define reality,"},{"time":950000,"text":"and force the rest of the pack to accept that reality"},{"time":953000,"text":"and follow the rules."},{"time":955000,"text":"The rules change all the time, but they always benefit them,"},{"time":958000,"text":"and in this case, the trickle-down effect,"},{"time":961000,"text":"which does not work in economics, works perfectly."},{"time":964000,"text":"Abuse trickles down from the top of the ladder to the bottom."},{"time":968000,"text":"Women and children, especially the poor, are at the bottom."},{"time":972000,"text":"Even the most destitute of men have someone they can abuse --"},{"time":975000,"text":"a woman or a child."},{"time":978000,"text":"I'm fed up with the power that a few exert over the many"},{"time":982000,"text":"through gender, income, race, and class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"I think that the time is ripe to make fundamental changes"},{"time":989000,"text":"in our civilization."},{"time":990000,"text":"But for real change, we need feminine energy"},{"time":993000,"text":"in the management of the world."},{"time":995000,"text":"We need a critical number of women in positions of power,"},{"time":998000,"text":"and we need to nurture the feminine energy in men."},{"time":1002000,"text":"I'm talking about men with young minds, of course."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Old guys are hopeless; we have to wait for them to die off."},{"time":1008000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1011000,"text":"Yes, I would love to have Sophia Loren's long legs"},{"time":1015000,"text":"and legendary breasts."},{"time":1017000,"text":"But given a choice, I would rather have the warrior hearts"},{"time":1020000,"text":"of Wangari Maathai, Somaly Mam, Jenny and Rose Mapendo."},{"time":1025000,"text":"I want to make this world good."},{"time":1028000,"text":"Not better, but to make it good."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Why not? It is possible. Look around in this room --"},{"time":1036000,"text":"all this knowledge, energy, talent and technology."},{"time":1041000,"text":"Let's get off our fannies, roll up our sleeves"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and get to work, passionately,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"in creating an almost perfect world."},{"time":1050000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}